com.impinj.octane

Enum ReportMode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ReportMode>
      • com.impinj.octane.ReportMode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ReportMode>

    public enum ReportMode
extends java.lang.Enum<ReportMode>
    The reader has several ways it can generate the tag reports that result from reader inventory operations.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      BatchAfterStop
      In this mode, the reader will collect and coalesce tag reports and send them the the current operation completes and the reader stops.
      Individual
      In this mode, the reader will send each tag observation as an individual report.
      WaitForQuery
      In this mode, the reader will hold and coalesce reports for the same tag.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • WaitForQuery

        public static final ReportMode WaitForQuery
        In this mode, the reader will hold and coalesce reports for the same tag. Reports will be held by the reader until the application issues a command to transmit the reports
        See Also:
        ImpinjReader.queryTags()

      • Individual

        public static final ReportMode Individual
        In this mode, the reader will send each tag observation as an individual report. No coalescing of tag reads is performed. Careful, you can get hundreds or even one thousand per second.

      • BatchAfterStop

        public static final ReportMode BatchAfterStop
        In this mode, the reader will collect and coalesce tag reports and send them the the current operation completes and the reader stops.
